<br>
About your only chance is is to wait until the NTOV named are dead and bard/da run there.  <br>
<br>
Faction means nothing in NTOV.  Once you get to Aary everything is KOS.  And from the NTOV pit to POM is a long ways.  Down around the ledges in the caverns, down the hall pass the intersection and then to the corner where the tiny zone in to POM is.  <br>
There are several wandering flurry drakes that path right through there.  Not to mentions the Triplets are all in that area as well.<br>
<br>
Wish ya luck.  But if you think you can just take a group of 6 ppl there walk in, coth/run/invis/ whatever and get there you have very little shot.<br>
<br>
Best bet is a bard run.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aailin>Aailin </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/15/03 10:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm59.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=665.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Again</span><hr size=1> &quot;You will need Ally with the dragons of NtoV. If you wish to join in on this im sure we could go to Kael and Kill a lot of giants to get you Max ally.&quot;<br>
